On Mon, 22 Mar 1999, Dave Cinege wrote:
> Alex Holden wrote:
> > 
> > On Sun, 21 Mar 1999, Dave Cinege wrote:
> > > Linux 2.2 has been doing it's impression of Windows NT on my box.
> > > Something I noticed with 2.2 is my bogomips are no longer even. Normal?
> > 
> > Have you tried pulling the CPU which is different to what it used to be?
> > If that fixes it, try borrowing another from somewhere and putting that in
> > it's place. It definitely sounds like a dodgy CPU to me...
> 
> Don't think so. I'm not seeing any such freezes with 2.0.36.
> It also reports 450.56 bogomips for each CPU. 2.2.3 reports 448.92/450.56.
Have you tried putting the CPU clocks back to the rated values for your
chips?  It may well be that 2.2.x is tighter in its timing tolerances
than 2.0.x as it handles stacked interrupts.  I'm assuming that you're
still overclocking everything as a matter of religion...
